This paper is primarily focused on the development of dependable robotics control software, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of specification languages and patterns for mission synthesis, verification, and simulation, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of temporal logic for mission specification, which is a topic related to systems and control (cs.SY) and programming languages (cs.PL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO, followed by cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SY, and cs.PL.
